			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Issues Updated<a name="59698"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 30 04 9:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It seems to me that SOE doesn't know what to do with bards.  We aren't really comparable to any other class: although we do something of almost every class, we do it in a completely different way.
<br />

<br />
So, we have some fantastic benefits and some pretty annoying drawbacks, but right now I suspect they see us as not really broken, so why fix us?  Especially since we don't fit any other mold.  We're an anomaly as a class, our problems are anomalies, our advantages are anomalies... we're in the &quot;too hard&quot; basket and they're probably glad we aren't actually a major problem!
<br />

<br />
Someone intentionally made the bard unique in gameplay, not just in abilities... some things might not have been forseen, like the AE kiting of 50+ mobs, but the bard isn't so different simply by blind luck and the development, by the players, of the way the class is played.  The bard is different because the class <i>was designed that way</i>.  I can't really believe that it happened any other way.
<br />

<br />
I'm not really arguing for or against any fixes to any of our &quot;top 10&quot; issues, or for or against any nerfs.  As I see it, SOE is, quite rationally, more interested in playing off the unfair advantages against the unfair drawbacks than they are in making everything fair.  And, the bard is <i>reasonably</i> (if not perfectly) well-balanced in that respect.  There are some things which are just annoying, and it'd be nice if they could fix them, but most of the other things seem to be requests for our unfair disadvantages to be removed while hoping they won't touch our unfair advantages.  Unless someone at SOE has a brain explosion, that ain't gonna happen!
<br />

<br />
As I see it, if they give every bard better melee abilities, we can kiss our solo, mass kiting abilities goodbye.  It seems to me that there's a direct trade-off here, in the developers' and the live team's minds, between being physically weak and tactically strong.  I really, really hope that we don't just automatically get improved melee and an accompanying AE nerf, because it removes the choice from our gameplay.  
<br />

<br />
My preference would be the creation of a new AA &quot;focus&quot;, with several levels that allow you to swap (perhaps permanently) the range of PBAoE songs (and perhaps our charm? sorry swarmers!) for improved melee ability.  Then, die-hard AE fans can live without better melee (as they've done all along), and die-hard melee fans can sacrifice their AE abilities for the dream of tanking.  Hmm... I might just /feedback that! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
