				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bard Issues Updated<a name="59914"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 1 04 10:20 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>SoE is a big company.  But the development team is rather tiny.  How many developers are there really?  5?  6?
<br />

<br />
Claiming issues can be fixed in 5 minutes is just untrue.  *Some* code changes can be made in 5 minutes, but, issues aren't nescisarily about code fixes.  Some are design issues which need to be discussed by devs and designers.
<br />

<br />
Lets assume an issue takes 1 hour to discuss between 5 people (some will take 5 minutes, some will have heated discussions that will go on for hours).  Considering you have 18 lists (16 class, 1 pvp, 1 tradeskills), it would take 180 hours to disucss the issues.  That translates to 22.5 working days which translates into 1 working month assuming the devs are doing nothing else.
<br />

<br />
That is a lot of time to commit just to class lists and nothing else.
<br />

<br />
While most of us see theses issues as cut and dry, resolving them isn't always the best thing for EQ as a whole.  Bards have class issues and some may never be resolved becuase that is one of the drawbacks of being a bard.  We can't have all positives and no negatives (just like every other class).
<br />

<br />
About only having 9 issues: I was out on vacation when they updated the list.  I didn't get a chance to add in a 10th issue, but was able to remove one that was pretty much complete.  After coming back and seeing that nothing is really going to be done till after OoW release, I decided not to persue adding a 10th issue becuase after OoW all our issues may change.  If the top 9 issues are resolved, I think we'd be pretty happy (even without a 10th one listed).
<br />

<br />
Lastly, the top 10 list is not a wish list.  It's an issues list and putting wish list items (especially unreasonable ones) will either be completely ignored or rejected right away.  Bugs on our top 10 list will get more attention wishes on other classes lists.</span></td>
