				<td colspan="2"><span>For all the years I've played EQ, these issues, certainly melee damage/mitigation have been there will always be, but I've never ever really thought of us as broken or lacking in any way.  
<br />

<br />
There have been only a few times that I can think where we were really screwed up, and the most recent two were:
<br />

<br />
1) The day and half group songs didn't work.  (First day of Luclin relesase)
<br />
2) The week instrument mods didn't apply to our songs (About a year ago?  Maybe longer.)
<br />

<br />
I started this game with a but nekkid bard, a noob sword and a piece of paper to guive to my guild leader.  I teethed on Orc 1 and the NRO Derv camps.  My first full suit of armor was banded, which I slowly replaced with bronze or Lambent in my late twenties.  I moved to Kunark when everybody else did, lvled in OT, then Dreadlands, then KC, then Sebilis and when it came time to set sail for the frozen wasteland I met my first GD frost giants in lambent/seb scale, maybe 1 or 2 pieces of Singing Steel, armed with SSoY and a Sioniche's Partisan.  My instruments were MMBD, Mino horn, gypsy lute, vendor horn.
<br />

<br />
I never had a problem.  I almost always got groups, and when I couldn't, soloing was never an issue.  The only role I haven't been able to fill in a group is main healer, and that's it.  I have been called upon many a time to be a group's MT, and as long as the group knows how let me keep agro, it's never an issue.  I have to say one of my favorite LDoN combos is me, healer, bst/sham, and any combo of three mag/nec/wiz.
<br />

<br />
To me, the only real problem for a bard is when he/she doesn't know how to play their class.
<br />

<br />
Dlan
<br />

<br />

<br />

